cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with deep learning applied to medical images, specifically using cinematic rendering to generate photorealistic images for training deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of synthetic data and fine-tuning of networks also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of medical imaging data suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
